22 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 15, Chapter 45, Subchapter 1, is
23 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
24 15-45-102. Wind power device height prohibition for waterfowl
25 conservation — Legislative findings — Definitions.
26 (a) The General Assembly finds that:
27 (1) Wind energy from wind farms and wind turbines is becoming an
28 increasingly large source of energy production throughout the nation;
29 (2) However, wind energy can have effects on wildlife and the
30 environment with birds, especially migratory birds like waterfowl, being at a
31 high risk of being impacted by wind power devices through collisions,
32 disorientation, and interference with seasonal migration;
33 (3) One way to minimize the impacts of wind energy on birds is
34 to keep wind power devices away from large concentrations of birds;
35 (4) The waterfowl populations in Arkansas have been declining in
36 recent years and may be greatly impacted by increased wind power devices in
