5 (b) As used in this section:
6 (1) "Bird band" means a federal bird band, auxiliary marker, or
7 color marker that is:
8 (A) Placed on a bird's leg;
9 (B) Used to study and identify individual birds; and
10 (C) Reported to the United States Geological Survey if the
11 bird is found or killed; and
12 (2) "Wind power device" means a device, including a windmill,
13 wind farm, or wind turbine, that is designed to use the kinetic energy of
14 moving air to provide mechanical energy or to produce electricity.
15 (c) On and after the effective date of this section, a wind power
16 device is prohibited from exceeding one hundred fifty feet (150 ft.) in
17 height if the wind power device is located within an area that is one hundred
18 square miles (100 sq. mi.) in which eleven (11) or more bird bands have been
19 collected in the previous ten (10) years.
20 (d) This section shall not apply to a wind farm or wind power device
21 if the wind farm or wind power device is under construction or is in
22 operation before January 1, 2025.
23
24 SECTION 2. EMERGENCY CLAUSE. It is found and determined by the
25 General Assembly of the State of Arkansas that wind energy can have
26 detrimental effects on wildlife and the environment with birds being at a
27 greater risk of being impacted by wind power devices; that waterfowl
28 populations in this state are declining and immediate conservation is needed
29 to ensure that the waterfowl populations increase; and that this act is
30 immediately necessary to ensure conservation of waterfowl populations in this
31 state as preserving waterfowl populations contributes to the economy of this
32 state through tourism and hunting activities which directly impacts the
33 citizens of this state. Therefore, an emergency is declared to exist, and
34 this act being immediately necessary for the preservation of the public
35 peace, health, and safety shall become effective on:
36 (1) The date of its approval by the Governor;
